# §22.5.9 for_each over a DAG-dependent probe chain (COOK-64 / CS-0091)
# Uses the native `probe` DSL (COOK-69).
#
# A realistic data-driven build: render one config file per microservice
# straight from a JSON manifest. The twist this example exercises is the
# *probe chain* — the `for_each` source is a probe that REQUIRES an upstream
# probe (`inputs.requires`), so the register pre-pass (§22.5.9) must resolve
# the whole chain, in dependency order, before the recipe fans out.
#
#   services_raw  — reads the manifest file.
#   services      — requires services_raw; enriches each record with a derived
#                   `url` field (read from the upstream probe via cook.cache.get).
#   render        — for_each over `services` (the DEPENDENT probe).
#
# What this demonstrates:
#   * Data-driven fan-out: one unit per manifest record (add a service → a new
#     unit appears; the DAG does not grow dynamically — it is sized at register).
#   * DAG-dependent probe pre-pass: `services` is evaluated only after its
#     `requires` upstream `services_raw`, with the upstream's fingerprint folded
#     into the dependent probe's fingerprint (§22.5.3).
#   * Per-member cache (§17.1 observable #5): edit one service in the manifest
#     and only that service's config rebuilds — the rest are cache hits, even
#     though the whole probe chain re-evaluates the member set.
#
# Run:
#   cook render            # fans out one config per service
#   ./verify.sh            # asserts codegen shape + execution + per-member cache

# Layer 1 — read the raw manifest. The `ingredients` line declares a file input,
# so editing the manifest re-fingerprints this probe (and everything downstream).
probe services_raw
    ingredients "data/services.json"
    produce as json { cat data/services.json }

# Layer 2 — the for_each source. Depends on `services_raw` via the header dep
# list; reads the upstream value with cook.cache.get and derives a `url` per
# record. The register pre-pass resolves `services_raw` first, then this, then
# sizes the fan-out from the returned array.
probe services: services_raw
    produce >{
        local out = {}
        for _, svc in ipairs(cook.cache.get("services_raw")) do
            table.insert(out, {
                name     = svc.name,
                url      = "http://localhost:" .. svc.port,
                replicas = svc.replicas,
            })
        end
        return out
    }

# One rendered config per service. `$<in.FIELD>` interpolates the enriched
# record's fields; `$<out>` is the per-member output path.
recipe render
    for_each services
    cook "build/$<in.name>.conf" using {
        mkdir -p build
        printf 'service  = %s\nurl      = %s\nreplicas = %s\n' \
            "$<in.name>" "$<in.url>" "$<in.replicas>" > $<out>
    }
